    "It represented many new emerging technologies and their use in industrial operations.",
    "One of the roles of this initiative was to assemble a collection of emerging digital technologies-not only AI, but v vi Foreword machine learning, internet of things, augmented reality, digital twins, cyber-physical systems, 3D printing, etc.",
    "[5]-and to orient these technologies in the directions of different manufacturing challenges.",
    "The 4th Industrial Revolution heralds the advent of internet and big data analysis methods within the industrial domain much as the 3rd Industrial Revolution in the 1980s began the introduction of computing and robotics in manufacturing.Challenge 1: Small Companies that often haven't deployed 3rd Industrial Revolution technologies let alone considered AI and other Industrie 4.0 technologies.The prevalence of small and medium sized (SME) manufacturers-in many countries up to 99.9% of all manufacturing companies [7]-with limited budget for system upgrades and limited in-house know-how means that the majority of industrial companies haven't been willing to consider investing in Industry 4.0 technologies to date.",
    "In fact, although many manufacturers today use some of the technologies linked to the 3rd Industrial Revolution (scheduling software, requirements planning systems, logic controllers etc."
